snippet.textDisplay: I am a musician and I always think about the blend that drives me away from every practical shits happening on earth and gives harmony and serenity through music. Indian music has curved out ways to fusion of classical and other genre, globalising the culture. But I must say that as a musician, I had always been waiting to learn more about the sounds and about the impact that a song could provide,which I had always found in Pakistan coke studio, every season. I am from Assam, India and here we have a lot to provide in music to the world and I wish if we collaborate with Pakistan musician, a lot can happen in terms of production quality and sound design. If it were possible, Arijit singh, singing Assamese traditional with the musicians of coke studio Pakistan.
